    {
      "type": "answer",
      "text": "I'll investigate your WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR with proper diagnostics. Let me run enterprise-grade root cause analysis using PowerShell and Python tools.",
      "timestamp": 1783146185920
    },
    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "The user has a BSOD with \"WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR\". They want me to:\n\n1. Investigate using enterprise root cause analysis\n2. Give a fixability score using iFix\n3. Tell how reliable it is\n4. Whether they can improve PC temperature5. All components are okay but they don't want to stress test\n6. Want a decent assessment using PowerShell and Python tools\n\nLet me first understand the WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR and then create diagnostic scripts.\n\nWHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR is a hardware-related error. Common causes:\n- CPU issues (overheating, overclocking instability, voltage issues)\n- RAM issues\n- Motherboard issues\n- PSU issues\n- Driver issues\n\nLet me create PowerShell and Python diagnostic scripts to check:\n1. System event logs for WHEA errors\n2. Temperature readings\n3. System information\n4. Memory diagnostics\n5. Disk health\n\nI'll start by creating diagnostic scripts.",
      "timestamp": 1783146198342
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "bash",
      "code": "{\"command\": \"Get-WinEvent -LogName System -MaxEvents 100 | Where-Object {$_.Id -eq 41 -or $_.Id -eq 18 -or $_.ProviderName -like '*WHEA*'} | Select-Object TimeCreated, Id, LevelDisplayName, Message | Format-Table -AutoSize\", \"description\": \"Check WHEA error events in system logs\"}",
      "output": "(no output)",
      "status": "success",
      "timestamp": 1783146201028
    },
